e results, which\nare of independent interest, establish estimates on $L^p(w)$, and also on\n$L^p(v\\,dw)$ with $v\\in A_\\infty(w)$, for the associated semigroup, its\ngradient, the functional calculus, the Riesz transform, and square functions.\nAs an application, we solve some unweighted $L^2$-Dirichlet, Regularity and\nNeumann boundary value problems for degenerate elliptic operators.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Oct 2015 00:01:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Oct 2015 17:06:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2015 12:54:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 26 May 2016 14:53:07 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 6 Oct 2016 08:05:48 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 7 Jun 2017 04:37:07 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 31 Oct 2017 05:39:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-10"}
